    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices in the form of a wheel, sometimes spiked, used for torture or execution by breaking the victim's bones or tearing flesh; in use from antiquity into early modern times.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
